FBIS3-56379 "drsov011_a_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS TU Leader Satisfied With 14 Jan Talks With Clinton LD1401185494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1453 GMT 14 Jan 94 LD1401185494 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Chairman of Russia's Independent Union of Miners, Aleksandr Sergeyev, told Interfax on Friday that "he is satisfied with the discussion that a group of union leaders conducted with President Bill Clinton at a formal reception in the U.S. ambassador's residence in Moscow on Thursday." In his words, at a brief meeting the sides touched upon the problems of the workers' movement in Russia at a time of economic reform, international cooperation between free unions, and prospects of its development. At the end of the meeting, according to Sergeyev, Clinton instructed one of his aides to prepare a detailed report on the world trade union movement.
